A2B4C6D8.name: Weird dream about clementines
A2B4C6D8.entry:
I had this weird dream where I was back in school, and for some reason, clementines were everywhere. Like, seriously, they were all over the place. In the halls, classrooms, you name it. It was as if clementines were the new cool thing.
In one class, the teacher was giving a lecture on how to peel clementines like a pro. Stud ents were huddled around their desks, practicing their peeling skills, and it was like a competition to get the perfect clementine peel.
And guess what was on the cafeteria menu? Clementine salad, clementine juice, and even clementine pizza. The whole school had gone clementine crazy, and it got me thinking, what's the deal with all these clementines?
When I woke up, I couldn't help but wonder if my dream was trying to tell me something. Maybe it was a reminder that even in the most ordinary places, you can stumble upon the unexpected and explore hidden connections. Weird dream, but it left me thinking about the strangest stuff.

K2L4M6N8.name: Arguments at school
K2L4M6N8.entry:
So, today at art school, things got pretty wild. We were having this intense argument about the role of art in society, and it got heated.
Basically, we had two warriors in the ring: Alex and Sarah. Alex was all about art being a direct commentary on social issues, while Sarah thought art should be your personal escape from reality. They went at it so hard that they were basically yelling at each other, and the whole room got divided.
I was caught in the middle, trying to keep the peace, but it was like trying to stop a runaway train. Artists can be seriously passionate about their beliefs and the meaning of their work.
In the end, we didn't really resolve anything, and the tension kind of hung in the air. But that's part of the whole art school experience, right? You've got to hear different viewpoints, even if it leads to some epic clashes. Hopefully, we can tackle these debates in a more chill way next time.
